			<ns0:name>robertm@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/robertm@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">llc is not only slow but also consumes a lot of memory.
A 100MB pexe takes 6min to process and consumes &amp;gt; 5GB in the process.

This severely limits the sizes pexes that can be translated in
a sandbox.

Note: When using this patch:
http://codereview.chromium.org/9240026
and using  -disable-global-opts there is no much reason
for llc to keep lots of bitcode information around for a function once it has been processed. But there could still lots of MC related data-structures.

